The Quasi Portable Binary Archive (QPBA)
========================================

Change Log


2011-03-16 FM:
	* First release as a subpart of the 'datatools' package
	at LPC Caen (SuperNEMO research group on neutrino physics)
	* Depends on Boost 1.44.0.
	* Use the 'boost::archive' namespace
	* The "boost/archive/basic_archive.hpp" defines the following classes :
		- library_version_type
		- version_type
		- class_id_type
		- class_id_reference_type (through BOOST_ARCHIVE_STRONG_TYPEDEF)
		- class_id_optional_type (through BOOST_ARCHIVE_STRONG_TYPEDEF)
		- object_id_type
		- object_reference_type (through BOOST_ARCHIVE_STRONG_TYPEDEF)
		- tracking_type
	The "boost/serialization/collection_size_type.hpp" defines also:
		- collection_size_type
	and "boost/serialization/item_version_type.hpp" defines:
		- item_version_type

	All  types above  are  given "[i/o]archive::save/load"  overloaded
	methods  to  ensure  portable  (de)serialization of  the  integral
	attributes within these classes.

